cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CE 

The paper presents a novel approach for automatic retrosynthesis route planning using a combination of a linguistic model and hyper-graph exploration strategy. The linguistic model is based on the transformer architecture, which is commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks, suggesting a potential fit for the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also introduces new metrics to evaluate the performance of the single-step retrosynthetic models, which could be relevant to the cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of the transformer architecture for reaction classification and the hyper-graph exploration strategy could be relevant to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) sub-categories, respectively.
